## 5ï¸âƒ£ Infinite Scroll Loader

**â“ Problem:**
Detect when the user scrolls to the bottom of the page and load new content dynamically.

**âœ… Solution:**

```html
<div id="content"></div>

<script>
const content = document.getElementById("content");

// add initial items
for (let i = 1; i <= 10; i++) {
  content.innerHTML += `<p>Item ${i}</p>`;
}

let count = 11;
window.addEventListener("scroll", () => {
  if (window.innerHeight + window.scrollY >= document.body.offsetHeight) {
    // load more items
    for (let i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
      content.innerHTML += `<p>Item ${count++}</p>`;
    }
  }
});
</script>
```

**ğŸ¯ Concept Tested:** `scroll` event, dynamic DOM updates.

